?    Our Emergency Response Program (ERP) (SOP GI10); includes Spill Containment and an  "in-house" emergency response HAZMAT Team (SOP QMD08) and is supported by local Incident and Emergency Response Contractors;



?    Process Safety Information (SOP GI20) is maintained on ammonia and other hazardous materials;



?    A Hazard Risk Assessment (SOP GI21)  is conducted periodically to ensure adequacy of controls, and processes; 



?    The Preventive Maintenance Program (SOP OP09) ensures the mechanical integrity of the equipment and its pressure relief and vapor control systems continue to operate as designed; 



?    Operating SOP's (OP02) provides all personnel with the information necessary to safely transport and store equipment;



?    Contractors or visitors working on our Depot facility require a Work Permit (SOP OD19) provided by the QHSSE Team. As part of the SOP, all visitors are briefed on the hazards and safety requirements of the job; and are trained to respond in case of release (Safety Briefing SOP GI-05);



?    Hot Work Permits (SOP OD17) are required whenever welding, cutting, grinding or other activities are conducted that could generate sparks and start a fire;



?    Formal Incident Investigations (SOP GI29) are conducted for incidents involving any and all releases and near misses that endanger employees or the public; 



?    Compliance Audits (SOP QMD03) are conducted periodically to ensure that the prevention program is meeting its objectives; 



?    QHSSE -  Management System (PL-041) is in place as Flexitank Quality Policy;

?    Management of Change (MOC) under SOP AD32 is in place to ensure project success, avoid loss of employees or customer's due to changes and minimize the impact on productivity



?    Pre-TRIP Safety Review (PTSR) are created "custom made" for ammonia  and other hazardous products or substances. (SOP OD03/0D09)



